title: For Sale:  1943 Mosin-Nagant 91/30 PU Sniper WWII (RGuns)
location: SW Metro, Minneapolis / St. Paul, Minnesota
postcontent:
This is a1943 Izhevsk Mosin Nagant 91/30 PU Sniper rifle. I purchased it from RGuns back in 2011, cleaned off the cosmoline, and it’s been stored in the gun cabinet (bolt open but de-cocked; garrison style) ever since. I never fired it and only took it out every spring to renew the gun oil as I do with all my “safe queens.” The optics are clear and the bore is very good if not excellent. The scope serial number is stamped on the left of the barrel shank and begins with (43) indicating 1943 manufacture. Some hieroglyphic precedes the serial number on the scope, I don’t know what it means. The actual serial number of the rifle has an alpha-prefix of (BT). The rifle is all matching (receiver, butt-plate, magazine floor-plate, bolt). The RGUNS mark is on the top of the barrel shank right above where the bolt meets the receiver. This is really all the information I have, i.e. there are no (MO) marks, Finnish marks, or any other marks from any non-Soviet countries. It’s just a plain-Jane 1943 PU. These are the only pictures available. The RGuns PU rifles were well researched by the collector community and regarded as genuine (i.e. non-bubba fakes). There’s LOTS of discussion on these rifles on the regular collector forums online.
 
The rifle comes with the original company receipt (with serial number), sling and bayonet, and the hard case that it come from RGuns in. The sale price is the receipt price (from back in 2011) plus the transfer I paid ($860 total). The price is FIRM. The only trade I'll consider is for a new or gently used Tavor SAR-18, otherwise cash only. Local sales only, thanks for looking.
